content.problemStatement:
Which of the following code snippets correctly demonstrates the scope of a loop variable declared inside a for loop in C?

**A.**
```c
int main() {
    for (int i = 1; i <= 3; i++) {
        printf("%d\n", i);
    }
    printf("%d", i);
    return 0;
}
```

**B.**
```c
int main() {
    int i;
    for (i = 1; i <= 3; i++) {
        printf("%d\n", i);
    }
    printf("%d", i);
    return 0;
}
```

**C.**
```c
int main() {
    for (int i = 1; i <= 3; i++) {
        printf("%d\n", i);
    }
    int i = 10;
    printf("%d", i);
    return 0;
}
```

**D.**
```c
int main() {
    for (int i = 1; i <= 3; i++) {
        printf("%d\n", i);
    }
    printf("%d", i + 1);
    return 0;
}
```

